{
  "transcript_id": "10587.7",
  "source_file": "10587.7.json",
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "chunk_words_setting": 800,
  "n_chunks": 3,
  "sentences": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "To Dachau.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Captivity"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when we were striked and bombed by the American mustangs, the squad leader finally realized what this-- what has been happening.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Captivity"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So they stopped shooting.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Captivity"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he flew very, very low with a white handkerchief and-- and to apologize for what he-- what they have done.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Captivity"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we proceeded.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Captivity"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "However, before we proceeded, there was like a mass grave that we dug.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Captivity"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we buried all the bodies there.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Captivity"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And-- and when it got very close to closing the grave, they-- they start killing the people, the ones that were putting the-- covering the grave up.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Captivity"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I was one of the people working on the graves, because I tried to run away.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Captivity"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "That was my punishment.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Captivity"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "However, there was-- an order was given by an officer to stop everything, and to evacuate immediately.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Captivity"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we proceeded into Dachau.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Captivity"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So I was very lucky that I was at the other end, because a lot of people were just shot-- one bullet in the hat and they pushed them into the grave.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Captivity"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So at Dachau, it was a horrible place.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Captivity"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were 32,000 prisoners in Dachau.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Captivity"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were squeezed together like herring, lying on the bunks.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Captivity"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the conditions were very bad.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Captivity"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And people were very sick and very tired.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Health"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Every day, there was a transport taken out of Dachau, because the crematoriums could not keep up with the mass graves, mass destruction.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Captivity"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- and they would take people into the mountains in-- in Bavaria and bring all those bodies back that were froze and starved.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Captivity"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and Dachau was--",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Captivity"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, they took people, human beings.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Captivity"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And stuck them into the open cars, rail cars.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Captivity"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they took them to the-- to the hills-- to the mountains.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Captivity"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "To die.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Captivity"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they brought them back frozen, dead.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Captivity"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And a lot of people died this way too, because in Dachau-- when Dachau was liberated, there was mountains of bodies that were piled like you would pile rock, mountains of rock or bags, or whatever.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Liberation"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Like pyramids of bodies in Dachau.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Captivity"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And--",
      "recall": false,
      "topics": []
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "recall": false,
      "topics": []
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "recall": false,
      "topics": []
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We didn't.",
      "recall": false,
      "topics": []
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they give you a piece of bread and send you on the transport.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Daily life (imprisonment)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so Jack and I, my cousin and I, we were already old hands at it.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Daily life (imprisonment)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we used to get in line and get the bread, and bring it back to the other guys.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Daily life (imprisonment)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we were very lucky that we were able to do this.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Daily life (imprisonment)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So we got a little bit more food.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Daily life (imprisonment)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then when the-- the American--",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Captivity"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A few weeks.",
      "recall": false,
      "topics": []
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then we were liberated four days after my 18th birthday.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Liberation"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was some birthday-- April 29.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Other"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they made another mistake, because they opened up all the supplies of food and gave it to these people that were skinny.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Post-conflict"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Their stomach shrank, and they-- and all ate rich food.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Health"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we lost a few thousand people the first week.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Post-conflict"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Then they realized what was happening.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Post-conflict"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So they shut the supplies down.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Post-conflict"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the-- and they were-- I went to see an officer to tell him that I want to join the army, and I want to go fight the Germans.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Government"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so he says, pick up the rifle.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Government"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I couldn't pick up the rifle.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Government"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I weighed 86 pounds.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Health"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we finally walked out of Dachau.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Liberation"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We walked into Munich.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Liberation"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we went to Adolf Hitler Platz, the seven of us.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Liberation"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Well, Adolf Hitler house-- Adolf Hitler's house, because it became the-- the American army made their headquarters there.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Government"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we said, we have no place to go.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Post-conflict"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We want to go to Adolf Hitler Platz, house, I'm sorry.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Post-conflict"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he says, take him and let him take a bath.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Post-conflict"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Give him clothes, and give him some food.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Post-conflict"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Well they took us down to the cellar.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Post-conflict"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my God, I-- my eyes.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Feelings and thoughts"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I saw the oranges, the apples, and the fruit, and the food.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Post-conflict"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I went crazy.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Feelings and thoughts"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that's how we went-- we got out of Dachau.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Liberation"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was this constant turmoil where people were asking of other people.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Feelings and thoughts"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I found out that they were alive, and they are in [NON-ENGLISH], which is outside of Breslau, probably not far from [NON-ENGLISH] area.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Refugee experiences"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so I said, OK.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Other"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But there were no planes, no trains.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Refugee experiences"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I got together a suitcase of American whiskey, cigarettes, and all sorts of things that I could-- and I was just stopping the locomotives that would be a working locomotive, fixed railroad train.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Refugee experiences"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I went across the border in Schwarzwald, the Black Forest from-- from Munich, from Bavaria to Austria.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Refugee experiences"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then I walked myself down through Czechoslovakia.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Refugee experiences"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The [NON-ENGLISH], the Russians, that was the border that the Russians said, where is your-- you have no identification.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Government"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I--",
      "recall": false,
      "topics": []
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Through the Black Forest.",
      "recall": false,
      "topics": []
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then I was stopping convoys of Russian soldiers with American cigarettes, and get hitchhiked.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Captivity"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My brother and sister.",
      "recall": false,
      "topics": []
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And that's how I-- someone said, they are in-- but one of my sisters, actually she went to Buchenwald.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Captivity"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And from Buchenwald, they sent her already to Sweden for rehabilitation.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Captivity",
        "Post-conflict"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But the others were in this small community outside of Breslau.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Captivity"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I saw my brother.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Post-conflict"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And everyone told him that Mark was killed in Auschwitz-- my brother, Herman.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Captivity"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But Romek is alive, because he was four years or so older than I was.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Other"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And when he saw me, he passed out, because all this time he knew that I was dead.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Feelings and thoughts"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that's how we were reunited.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Post-conflict"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And there were some cousins.",
      "recall": false,
      "topics": []
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we went on a transport, after the war mind you, that they were re-expatriating the volksdeutsche-- you know, the Germans that didn't want to stay in Poland, because they will be killed.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Post-conflict",
        "Refugee experiences"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we became volksdeutsche.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Other"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we went straight to Munich from-- it took us a few days to get there.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Post-conflict"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Also in cattle car, but it was a different kind of a transport.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Post-conflict"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that's how we all arrived in Munich.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Post-conflict"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because we're running very short of time, which I apologize, and I'm sorry for, I think we'll do things a little differently than we normally do.",
      "recall": false,
      "topics": []
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Why don't you tell me first when you came to the United States?",
      "recall": false,
      "topics": []
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I came to the United States in December 23rd, 1949.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Refugee experiences"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And you met and married?",
      "recall": false,
      "topics": []
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I served in the army maybe two years between 1952 and '54.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Government"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The United States Army, I was drafted.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Government"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then after I got out of the Army two years later-- I met my-- a year later-- I met my lovely wife.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Other"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then a year later, we were married.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Other"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We were engaged-- it was a long engagement.",
      "recall": true,
      "topics": [
        "Other"
      ]
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Rhona-- Rhona Fiedler.",
      "recall": false,
      "topics": []
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "American-born in Detroit, Michigan.",
      "recall": false,
      "topics": []
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Detroit, Michigan.",
